						<p>I reviewed this recently, and... well, there's a certain inescapable charm in the woman's struggle, as bare life, as an animal, between the birthgiving sheep and the deathmarked horse. There's a certain boko haram beauty to the daughterless woman telling the motherless girl not to cry, because... well... There's indisputedly a frank yet warm, warmly forcible rendition of the strings of female flesh. Tres recherche, of course, but then again how's one to make films otherwise ?</p>
<p>And Bene loves her, and she's not ashamed, and...</p>
						</li>

